# Tailwind CSS Conventions

## Critical Rules

### 1. ❌ NEVER Use "px" Units

**Always use "rem" units or Tailwind classes.**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Using px
<div className="min-h-[600px]">
<div style={{ height: "400px" }}>
<div className="h-[24px] w-[24px]">

// ✅ GOOD - Using rem or Tailwind classes
<div className="min-h-[37.5rem]">  // 600px = 37.5rem (16px base)
<div className="min-h-screen">      // Prefer Tailwind classes
<div className="size-6">            // 1.5rem = 24px
```

### 2. ✅ Always Prefer Tailwind Classes Over Arbitrary Values

**Use Tailwind's built-in classes instead of arbitrary values when possible. Always check if a Tailwind class exists before using arbitrary values.**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Arbitrary values when Tailwind class exists
<div className="h-[24px] w-[24px]">  // Use size-6 instead
<div className="min-h-[37.5rem]">    // Use min-h-150 instead
<div className="p-[16px]">            // Use p-4 instead
<div className="text-[14px]">        // Use text-sm instead

// ✅ GOOD - Tailwind classes
<div className="size-6">           // h-6 w-6
<div className="min-h-150">        // 37.5rem = 600px
<div className="p-4">              // 1rem = 16px
<div className="text-sm">          // 0.875rem = 14px
```

### 3. ✅ Use `size-*` Instead of `h-* w-*` for Square Elements

**When height and width are the same, use `size-*` class.**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Separate h and w
<div className="h-4 w-4">
<Icon className="h-6 w-6" />
<button className="h-8 w-8">

// ✅ GOOD - Use size
<div className="size-4">
<Icon className="size-6" />
<button className="size-8">
```

### 4. ✅ Prefer Semantic Classes Over Arbitrary Values

**Use Tailwind's semantic spacing, sizing, and typography classes.**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Arbitrary values
<div className="p-[12px] m-[8px] text-[16px]">

// ✅ GOOD - Semantic classes
<div className="p-3 m-2 text-base">
```

## Conversion Reference

### Common px to rem Conversions (16px base)

| px | rem | Tailwind Class |
|----|-----|----------------|
| 4px | 0.25rem | `p-1`, `m-1`, `gap-1` |
| 8px | 0.5rem | `p-2`, `m-2`, `gap-2` |
| 12px | 0.75rem | `p-3`, `m-3`, `gap-3` |
| 16px | 1rem | `p-4`, `m-4`, `gap-4`, `text-base` |
| 20px | 1.25rem | `p-5`, `m-5`, `gap-5` |
| 24px | 1.5rem | `p-6`, `m-6`, `gap-6`, `size-6` |
| 32px | 2rem | `p-8`, `m-8`, `gap-8`, `size-8` |
| 40px | 2.5rem | `p-10`, `m-10`, `gap-10` |
| 48px | 3rem | `p-12`, `m-12`, `gap-12` |
| 64px | 4rem | `p-16`, `m-16`, `gap-16` |

### Size Classes

| Square Size | Tailwind Class |
|-------------|----------------|
| 16px × 16px | `size-4` |
| 20px × 20px | `size-5` |
| 24px × 24px | `size-6` |
| 32px × 32px | `size-8` |
| 40px × 40px | `size-10` |
| 48px × 48px | `size-12` |

## Examples

### ✅ Good Examples

```typescript
// Icons - use size
<ChevronLeft className="size-4" />
<Home className="size-6" />

// Containers - use semantic classes
<div className="min-h-screen p-8">
<div className="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

// Spacing - use Tailwind classes
<div className="space-y-4 p-6">
<div className="gap-4 flex items-center">

// Typography - use Tailwind classes
<p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
<h1 className="text-4xl font-bold">
```

### ❌ Bad Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Using px in arbitrary values
<div className="min-h-[600px]">
<div className="h-[24px] w-[24px]">
<div className="p-[16px]">

// ❌ Using h and w separately for squares
<Icon className="h-4 w-4" />

// ❌ Using inline styles with px
<div style={{ height: "400px", padding: "16px" }}>
```

## When Arbitrary Values Are Acceptable

Arbitrary values are acceptable **only** when:
1. No equivalent Tailwind class exists
2. You need a specific rem value not in Tailwind's scale
3. You're using CSS custom properties

```typescript
// ✅ Acceptable - No Tailwind equivalent
<div className="grid-cols-[200px_1fr]">

// ✅ Acceptable - Specific rem value (only if no Tailwind class exists)
<div className="min-h-[37.5rem]">  // Only if min-h-150 doesn't exist

// ✅ Acceptable - CSS custom property
<div className="bg-[var(--primary-color)]">
```

## Checklist

Before committing code, check:

- [ ] No `px` units in className or style props
- [ ] No arbitrary values like `h-[24px]` or `min-h-[600px]`
- [ ] Square elements use `size-*` instead of `h-* w-*`
- [ ] Prefer Tailwind semantic classes over arbitrary values
- [ ] Use `rem` if arbitrary values are necessary

## Summary

**Golden Rules:**

1. ❌ **NEVER use "px"** - Always use "rem" or Tailwind classes
2. ✅ **Prefer Tailwind classes** - Use built-in classes over arbitrary values
3. ✅ **Use `size-*`** - For square elements instead of `h-* w-*`
4. ✅ **Use semantic classes** - `p-4`, `m-2`, `text-base`, etc.
